# Setup Guide: HPD Calibration Automated Lead Generation

## 1. Prerequisites and Accounts
- Google [Sheets, Console] (for creating OAuth credentials)
- GitHub (enable Actions)
- Zapier/Make.com accounts (optional, for no-code workflows)
- API Keys: Hunter.io, Clearbit, OpenAI or HuggingFace, Socrata, HUDUser, HubSpot, Mailchimp, Twilio, Slack, Telegram
- (Optional) Railway/Heroku or similar if deploying on serverless

## 2. Setting Up Environment Variables
1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`
2. Fill in all API key values
3. Place Google Service Account JSON (for Sheets API) in repo root, default filename: `google-creds.json`. Download from Google Cloud Console.
4. **Never commit your `.env` or `google-creds.json` to version control.**

## 3. Google Sheets Integration
- [Create a Service Account](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials)
- Enable Google Sheets API
- Share your target Sheet with the service account email (found in the JSON)
- Enter the Sheet ID (from URL) in your `.env`

## 4. API Credentials
- **Hunter.io**: https://hunter.io/
- **Clearbit**: https://dashboard.clearbit.com/signup
- **OpenAI**: https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys
- **NYC Socrata**: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/
- **HUD Multifamily**: https://www.huduser.gov/portal/datasets/mf.html
- **HubSpot**: https://developers.hubspot.com/docs/api/overview
- **Mailchimp**: https://mailchimp.com/developer/
- **Twilio**: https://www.twilio.com/console
- **Slack**: https://api.slack.com/apps
- **Telegram**: https://core.telegram.org/bots

## 5. Install Python Dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## 6. One-click Deploy (Railway)
- Click the Deploy button in README or go to Railway dashboard
- Fill out all environment fields using your `.env` values
- Set repo auto-deploy and schedule in the Railway console

## 7. Running Locally (Manual)
```bash
python scripts/data_sourcing.py
python scripts/enrich_leads.py
python scripts/outreach.py
python scripts/ai_scoring.py
```

## 8. Enabling GitHub Actions
- Push to GitHub.
- Go to "Actions" tab, enable workflows.
- Edit `/workflows/github_scheduled.yaml` to customize schedule, set up secrets in your repo.

## 9. Setting Up Telegram Bot (Optional, for community networking)
- Create a bot using BotFather, get the token.
- Fill in `TELEGRAM_API_KEY` in your `.env`
- Run: `python scripts/community_bot.py`

## 10. Integrating No-Code Tools (Zapier/Make.com)
- Import `workflows/zapier_integration.json` into Zapier dashboard.
- Map fields to your Sheet, HubSpot, Mailchimp, and Slack workflows as needed.

## Troubleshooting
- Check logs in GitHub Actions/your server platform for errors.
- Verify API quotas & limits (free tiers have caps).
- For NYC-specific errors, validate addresses and data join logic.
